─ index.json        # article manifest\n│       └── *.md              # blog posts\n├── vendor/\n│   └── marked.min.js\n└── assets/\n    └── fonts/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Sequence\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation\n1. Create `index.html` with Mac window structure\n2. Implement CSS variables and design system\n3. Style Mac window chrome (traffic lights, title bar)\n4. Style terminal body with scrolling\n\n### Phase 2: Core Terminal\n5. Create `OutputRenderer.js` - line-by-line output\n6. Create `CursorManager.js` and blinking cursor CSS\n7. Create `InputHandler.js` - keyboard capture\n8. Create `TypeWriter.js` - typing animation engine\n\n### Phase 3: Command System\n9. Create `CommandRegistry.js` and `CommandProcessor.js`\n10. Implement basic commands: `help`, `clear`\n11. Implement `about` command with profile content\n12. Add clickable suggestions UI\n\n### Phase 4: Content System\n13. Add `marked.js` and create `MarkdownParser.js`\n14. Create `ContentLoader.js` for fetching .md files\n15. Create `ArticleIndex.js` with blog manifest\n16. Implement `blog` and `read` commands\n17. Style markdown output for terminal\n\n### Phase 5: Polish\n18. Create `InitSequence.js` - Claude Code startup animation\n19. Implement `HashRouter.js` for deep linking\n20. Add command history (up/down arrows)\n21. Implement `contact` and `skills` commands\n22. Mobile responsiveness and testing\n\n---\n\n## Key Features\n\n### Startup Sequence\n```\n> Initializing claude-code v1.0.0...\n> Loading personality matrix... done\n> Establishing neural pathways... done\n> Ready.\n\nWelcome! I'm Stefano's personal website.\nType 'help' for commands or click a suggestion.\n\n[about]  [blog]  [skills]  [contact]\n\n> _\n```\n\n### Available Commands\n- `help` - list commands\n- `about` - personal profile\n- `blog` - list articles\n- `read <slug>` - read article\n- `skills` - tech stack\n- `contact` - contact info\n- `clear` - clear terminal\n\n### Visual Style\n- Dark terminal theme (#0d1117 back