          "text": "# SettingsSentry: macOS Configuration Backup Tool\n\n## What It Does\n\nSettingsSentry is a lightweight command-line utility that \"backs up and restores your application settings\" for macOS systems. It enables users to preserve application configurations during system resets, migrations, or hardware issues.\n\n## Core Features\n\n- **Backup/Restore Operations**: Securely archives application settings and reinstates them to original locations\n- **Automated Scheduling**: Integrates with cron for automatic execution at system reboot or custom intervals\n- **Versioned Backups**: Creates timestamp-based backup directories (YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS format) allowing multiple retention versions\n- **Dry-Run Mode**: Previews operations without making actual system changes\n- **Encryption Support**: Optional AES-256-GCM password-based encryption for sensitive configurations\n- **ZIP Archive Option**: Packages backups as compressed archives instead of directories\n- **Environment Variable Support**: Expands variables in configuration paths (e.g., `${HOME}`, `${APP_NAME}`)\n- **Command Execution**: Runs pre/post backup and restore scripts defined in configuration files\n\n## Key Advantages Over Mackup\n\nThe tool addresses specific compatibility issues: \"Full compatibility with macOS Sonoma and future versions\" and avoids \"risk of overwriting settings via symlinks\" that plague its predecessor.\n\n## How It Works\n\nUsers define application configurations in `.cfg` files specifying:\n- Application name\n- Configuration file paths\n- Optional backup/restore commands\n- Environment variable placeholders\n\n## Installation & Use Cases\n\nDefault locations: `configs/` directory and `iCloud Drive/settingssentry_backups/`. Typical applications include syncing settings across machines, versioning preferences, and simplifying system recovery workflows.",
